mobs.long_desc: A chipmunk searches for bugs.
mobs.desc: This tiny creature has reddish-brown fur with white and black stripes along its sides.  Its long, fluffy tail swishes in the grasses as it tries to find some bugs to snack on.

mobs.long_desc: A brush hare is twitching its ears at you.
mobs.desc: This creature with greyish brown fur stares back at you with large dark eyes. The ears are huge in direct proportion to the rest of its body.  It looks ready to bolt at any moment, but lucky for you its feet are still gently thumping the ground.

mobs.long_desc: A golden mouse chews on some grain.
mobs.desc: This tiny golden creature has small black eyes, and its little nose sprouts several wiskers.  The mouse sits here trying to camouflage itself in the grasses.  Its golden fur helping to hide the tiny creature in the tall grasses.

mobs.long_desc: A dusty hawk circles above.
mobs.desc: The large bird of prey seems to be in search of a meal.  It has been successful, and you can see the blood tinged feathers around its beak.  The eyes of this hawk pierce the grasses and brush in search of prey.  This beast is a fierce hunter in this environment.

mobs.long_desc: A slender snake races through the grass.
mobs.desc: This snake is pretty long, and it seems to be built for speed.  The tiny brown scales all over its body grip everything in its path to help the racer speed its way through the grasses in search of prey.  This agile creature stops only long enough to check the air for details about its surroundings before heading on.

mobs.long_desc: A raccoon plays with something shiny.
mobs.desc: The face of this creature is covered in a mask of dark fur around its eyes, and white over the eye ridges and around the muzzle leaves a dark outline to the raccoon's mask.  Its long ringed tail is a little shorter than the rest of its body which is covered in grizzled greyish fur.  The raccoon blends in well with its surroundings, but it probably would not like being cornered.

mobs.long_desc: A rabid raccoon snarls at you with a foaming mouth.
mobs.desc: This masked creature looks to be troubled by its disease, and it seems to be in pain.  The once peaceful creature is angry, and you can see foam covering its mouth and face.  The small creature has a wild and dangerous look in its eyes.

mobs.long_desc: A brush finch searches for a worm.
mobs.desc: This tiny little bird is perched on a single blade of grass.  It must be light not to topple the thin grass, but then it is mostly feathers.  Its brown wings and chest blend well with the upper grasses, and the finch's watchful eyes are set on finding a nice meal in the grasses below.

mobs.long_desc: A lark perches near you preening its horns.
mobs.desc: The lark perches nearby, and it seems to be more interested in preening itself than anything you could be doing.  This is a male of the species, and the two horn shaped, clusters of feathers on its head make this an easy distinction. The rest of the lark's body is covered in mute brown feathers except for a long streak of black running from the sides of its beak down to a white spot on its breast.

mobs.long_desc: A lark takes to the sky in search of a mate.
mobs.desc: As this bird flies by it seems to be intent on finding something in the grasses below.  The lark lets out a few chirps every so often, and then she flies on. The feathers covering her body are brown, but there is a large white spot on her breast.  A small streak of black runs from the corner of her beak to the spot on her chest.

mobs.long_desc: A bullfrog croaks out a warning here.
mobs.desc: This amphibian is yellow-green with dark brown mottling.  The bullfrog's eyes stare back at you from its large head as it sits partially covered in mud. Although it seems small the bullfrog seems to mean business as well, and it looks as if it's almost taunting you.

mobs.long_desc: An earthworm stretches out to soak up some moisture here.
mobs.desc: You see a segmented, soft bodied worm aerating the soil as it digs. Purplish-orange in color and about five inches long, these worms love to come to the surface after a strong rain to play in the mud.

mobs.long_desc: A green snake slithers through the grasses.
mobs.desc: A small, slender snake with bright yellow eyes makes its way through the grasses.  There are no markings of any kind on its body, but the green scales match the grasses perfectly.  This feature helps this small snake survive in an area with so many predators around looking for a meal.

mobs.long_desc: A black squirrel hides among the low branches.
mobs.desc: A quick flick of a bushy tail, and a ripple of fur as the squirrel tenses on a branch are the only things that give this creature's hiding place away. Covered head to tail in black fur this rare creature hides among the branches trying to finish its meal.

mobs.long_desc: A grouse struts by ruffling its crest at you.
mobs.desc: Strutting near you, this reddish-brown feathered bird seems to be trying to get your attention for some reason.  The grouse fans its banded tail feathers at you, and ruffles the crest on its head to draw your eyes towards itself.

mobs.long_desc: A hummingbird hovers over a wildflower.
mobs.desc: A small bird hovers just above a blooming wildflower.  Its small wings beating in a figure eight pattern to keep it in place as it feeds off the nectar from the blooms.  The hummingbird is mostly covered in dark gray feathers, but there is a small patch of crimson just under its beak that stands out.

mobs.long_desc: A bluebird flies back to its nest.
mobs.desc: The wings of this small bird are covered in blue feathers, as are its back, tail, and head.  The only feathers not sharing that blue tint are the ones covering the bluebird's chest and neck.  Those feathers are dirty orange in color.  The bluebird moves easily through the air in these open spaces.

mobs.long_desc: A cardinal swoops in for a look around.
mobs.desc: A bird covered in red feathers flutters above the grasses.  A small mask of black feathers surrounds its red beak.  The bright red body stands out against the backdrop of the grasses as the cardinal searches for its food.

mobs.long_desc: A young fox prances through the grass.
mobs.desc: As the young fox prances near you its body moves with amazing grace.  The little legs of the fox simply trotting along while its tail seems to almost follow behind on its own accord.  At the slightest sound its ears perk up, and it gazes down a long snout towards you.  Pure survival instinct is all you see glaring back at you from this little creature.

mobs.long_desc: A big-eared bat hangs from the ceiling chirping softly.
mobs.desc: Short, black fur covers the body of this small, four inch long mammal.  The ears of this bat are what distinguish it from other species of bats.  They are huge in comparison with the rest of its body.  Growing to almost twice the length of the bat's body, they are by far the largest ears of any bats on this continent.

mobs.long_desc: A hellbender makes its home in a shallow pool.
mobs.desc: A thick salamander lies in a shallow pool of water breathing through gills on its neck.  The hellbender is almost two feet long, and its tail looks like a formidable weapon.  The salamander's dark skin is speckled with red, and its two black eyes are looking straight through you.

mobs.long_desc: A fat rat stumbles around, too stuffed to run away.
mobs.desc: A true image of a rodent's rodent, this rat has found an overabundance of food in the grasses.  Its small nose and its tail are the only features that are not bloated with fat.  You might not even recognize this creature for what it is at first glance, but look closely.  It's still a rat.

mobs.long_desc: A vole flicks its red whiskers at you.
mobs.desc: This relative of the rodent family is a little larger than your average rat, but it has much nicer features.  The vole's long red whiskers are unusual for rodents, but the slick, grey fur that covers its body is fairly common among the species.  This small vole is flashing its whiskers and giving you a good look at the two large teeth protruding well over its lower lip.

mobs.long_desc: A crow flies overhead as dark as night.
mobs.desc: A black feathered crow flies over you in search of some food.  Every feather on this bird is as black as the darkest night, and its beak is just as dark.  Two jet black eyes scan all around you, but they seem to be keeping an eye on the sky as well as the ground below.  Even the feet of this crow are black as tar.

mobs.long_desc: A speckled mouse feeds on some grains.
mobs.desc: This small rodent does its best to finish its meal despite your arrival. There is little doubt the mouse is hungry, but it seems to be healthy enough. The creature's fur is brown with small specks of tan covering its entire body. The tail is the only part, save its nose, not covered with the speckled fur.

mobs.long_desc: A man garbed in furs checks the ground for tracks.
mobs.desc: Standing six feet tall, this muscular man is dressed head to toe in cured furs. They seem to be a mixture of many different animals, but the outfit is complete.  He looks like he has lived off the land for some time now, and from the size of some of his pelts there is no doubt he is good with a knife.  The trapper is true grit tempered under the unyielding forces of nature.

mobs.long_desc: A crimson-bellied snake slithers among the grasses.
mobs.desc: Slithering through the grasses quietly in search of its next meal, this small crimson-bellied snake passes near your feet.  As it detects your presence the snake flips over offering its crimson belly to you.  It certainly looks to be dead, but it happened so fast.

objects.ground: A &6spring&0 of &6&bclear water&0 bubbles to the surface here.
objects.action_desc: Clear, drinkable water bubbles up through the ground here from an underground spring.

extras.text: Clear, drinkable water bubbles up through the ground from and underground spring.  The water is cool to the touch, and it forms a small pool here before overflowing into a stream to the east.

objects.ground: A small stash of seeds are piled here.

extras.text: A mixed pile of seeds from several different grasses and wildflowers.  They seem fresh and should make a tasty snack.

objects.ground: A small pile of fur lies here.

extras.text: This soft, fur vest has been made from several raccoon skins.  The vest allows for easy movement, and it still lends some protection to the wearer.

objects.ground: A black feather rests on the ground.

extras.text: A jet black feather is attatched by leather to a small silver hoop.  The hoop itself is tiny, and the feather seems to hang down from it.

objects.ground: A black-fur pouch has been left here.

extras.text: This pouch is made of the finest black fur that has been stitched together with slender leather straps to form this container.  Well made it seems like it should hold a good bit before filling.

objects.ground: A pile of golden fur has been dropped here.

extras.text: The leggings are soft and made to fit well around any wearer.  The fur is a gentle golden color, and the pair of leggings seems to be made up of many small creatures.

objects.ground: A polished piece of bone juts out from the ground.

extras.text: With a polished hilt of bone the knife has a good grip, and the blade is well balanced for easy cutting.  The knife has been kept sharp, and it is suited well for cutting through the hides of animals.

objects.ground: A pelt from a fox lies crumpled here.

extras.text: Cured with an expert hand this pelt has been made into a sturdy pair of sleeves.  They are a reddish tint and should provide good protection from the weather.

objects.ground: A tiny &6&bstream&0 trickles through the meadow.

extras.text: There is an image hovering just on the surface of the stream.  The figure looks familiar, but it's distorted by the flow so that there is just a blur.

objects.ground: A map with extra features on the back gathers dust here.

Pog's notes on the Brushland Region: Many creatures make these grasses their home. Abundant water in the southwest, and plenty of food make this area a haven for all sorts of creatures of the forest. My soul is happy to see this.

objects.ground: A red feather floats around on the breeze.

extras.text: This is the tailfeather of a red cardinal from the Brushlands west of the city of Anduin.  It would make a hondsome quill for a sorcerer who wants a little extra flair when scribing spells.

rooms.name: Off the Great Road
rooms.description: Frequent travel has made a small path here which can be followed rather easily.  The path picks its way through the rocky slopes just off the Great Road near the city of Anduin.  There are a many tracks mixed together in the dirt.  Many humanoid footsteps have passed by in recent days. The Great Road lies to the east, and the path continues west.

rooms.name: Near Anduin
rooms.description: Frequent travel has made a small path here which can be followed rather easily.  The path picks its way through the rocky slopes near the city of Anduin.  There are a many tracks mixed together in the dirt.  Many humanoid footsteps have passed by in recent days, and the sounds of city life echo out of natural vents in the mountainside. The path continues east and west.

rooms.name: A Bend in the Trail
rooms.description: Recent rock fall from the mountainside has partially covered the path, but passage is still possible.  Activity can be heard in the east, but the noises seem faint in this rocky section of the trail.  One large boulder stands out among the many smaller rocks. The path continue east and north.

extras.text: There is a huge rock slab lying here.  It looks to have fallen from the slope to the west, but there are so many other rocks littering the path its hard to tell for sure.

rooms.name: Around the Boulder
rooms.description: The path continues around the huge boulder to the west and south.  There are many tiny gray flakes of rock covering the path, but it has been travled well enough to cause no problem in following.

rooms.name: Base of a Steep Slope
rooms.description: You stand at the foot of a steep, rocky slope.  The great deal of debris all about your feet gives caution to any idea of climbing such a face, but you can just make out a ledge not far above you.  There is a well walked path leading off to the east from here.

rooms.name: Along a Game Trail
rooms.description: There are many tracks from different small animals in the dirt here.  You can follow the tracks to the north, or try sliding down a steep slope to another path there.

rooms.name: Along a Game Trail
rooms.description: Making your way through the steep hills, you find the help of this game trail a welcome aid in finding your way.  The path is easy to follow to the north and south.

rooms.name: A Bend in the Trail
rooms.description: The trail takes a sharp turn here, but with the help of the many small tracks in the dirt it is simple to find your way.  The trail continues to the west and south from here.  To the east lies the beginnings of a rank forest. In the distance to the north this forest is shrouded in shadowy trees and what appears to be many fallen ancient woods, now rotting and decaying.

rooms.name: Foot of a High Ridge
rooms.description: You find yourself standing at the foot of a high ridge.  A game trail heads off to the north from here, and there are a few tracks leading up the ridge as well.  It seems like you could make the ridge, and although it seems very high there are many cutbacks in the rock making it an easy climb.

rooms.name: On a High Ridge
rooms.description: The high ridge overlooks the surrounding rocky landscape below.  You can make your way down off the ridge here or head west out along the ridge.

rooms.name: On a High Ridge
rooms.description: This narrow ledge of rock only allows passage for one creature at a time, and the heights are staggering to the senses.  A fall from this ridge would be the end of even the healthiest of adventurers.  You can safely make your way along the ridge to the west and east.

rooms.name: A View from Above
rooms.description: The view from the ridge is wonderful from this spot.  The crags of the surrounding mountains are like razors running along the horizon.  To the west you glimps whats seems to be a golden sea glistening in the sunshine.  You can make your way towards it by heading down from here, or you can continue along the ridge to the east.

rooms.name: Tracks Near a Golden Sea
rooms.description: So many tracks in the area make it hard to follow any single creature.  You can see the edge of a clearing just to the west, and it seems many of the tracks lead into the grasses growing there.  You can also head into the hills to the east.

rooms.name: Edge of a Golden Sea
rooms.description: You find yourself on the edge of a huge brushfield.  The grasses here are young, and they have grown to only half of their full height.  Standing almost two feet tall they are a mix of green and dusty, yellow stalks.  The voices of nature surround you completely in the crisp air.  You can stay in the shorter grasses on the edge of the field to the west and south.

You can trek into the taller grasses to the west, or you can stay in the shorter grasses on the edge of the field to the north and south.

rooms.name: A Pile of Stones
rooms.description: Standing tall among the grasses here is a rather large pile of grey stones. The pile is almost two feet in diameter with a smaller tapered edge on the western side.  It seems to be a trail marker of some sorts, and it's pointing west into the thick golden grasses.

rooms.name: Tall Grasses
rooms.description: All around you dancing waves of golden grass sway in the breeze.  The grasses themselves stand over four feet tall, and the rays of the sun shimmer off of each blade in this vast sea of brush.  At your feet, the rustling of small creatures can be heard scampering from the shadow of a passing bird of prey.

At your feet, the rustling of small creatures can be heard scampering from the shadow of a passing bird of prey.

rooms.name: Edge of a Golden Sea
rooms.description: You find yourself on the edge of a huge brushfield.  The grasses here are young, and they have grown to only half of their full height.  Standing almost two feet tall they are a mix of green and dusty, yellow stalks.  The voices of nature surround you completely in the crisp air.  You can trek into the taller grasses to the north, or you can stay in the shorter grasses on the edge of the field to the east and west.

rooms.description: You are standing by the only tree you can see in this area.  It is a young oak, but it seems to be rather healthy to be standing alone here with nothing to protect it from the elements.  Its roots must go deep to support such a straight and tall young hardwood.  The oak provides the only shade in the meadow, and it seems the wildlife are fond of its acorns as well.

rooms.name: Near the Base of a Waterfall
rooms.description: The trench is fairly clear of brush here, but you can see the tangle of briars and scrub just north of you.  In the opposite direction there is a clear pool being feed by a small waterfall.  You can head down to the edge of the pool from here, or strike back into the thick brush of the trench.

rooms.name: Base of a Small Waterfall
rooms.description: Flowing water from the high ledge above you has formed a beautiful, cascading waterfall over the western wall.  The rocks here have all been worn smooth by the pounding waterfall, and several of them would be large enough to allow you to stretch out for a bit.  Just audible over the noise of the falls you can pick up soft chirping noises coming from behind the curtain of falling water.

extras.text: Gazing towards the waterfall you can see what looks to be an entrance to a cave just behind the curtain of water.  The waterfall looks small enough to walk through without much trouble.

rooms.name: A Cave Entrance
rooms.description: The mouth of this cave is large enough for several people, and strangely enough there is some illumination coming from mineral veins in the cave walls. You can see well once your eyes become adjusted to the lighting.  The sounds of a waterfall echo loudly here in the cave entrance, as water splashes in from the east.  You can see that the cave goes deeper to the west, but the veins of light continue in that direction as well.  Soft chirps echo from within the cave out into the fresh air to the east.

extras.text: The veins are about an inch thick, and each glows with a gentle yellow light. There are many of these mineral veins streaking the walls of this cave.

rooms.name: A Damp Cave
rooms.description: The cave walls are covered in veins of some mysterious mineral, but the glow given off by them provides light for the entire area.  The rocks here are all damp, and there are many pools of water covering the floor of the cave.  Your ears pick up the same soft chirps as well as the steady drips of water from the moist cave ceiling. The cave continues east and west.

extras.text: The veins are about an inch thick, and each glows with a gentle yellow light. There are many of these mineral veins streaking the walls of this cave.

rooms.name: A Root Coverd Ceiling
rooms.description: The cave opens up some here in this failry circular room, but there is still enough light coming from the mineral veins in the walls to light the area. The moisture has some help from a large cluster of thick roots growing out of the northwest corner of the ceiling, as the water trickles down to the cave floor.  Large puddles have formed about the cave floor from years of constant dripping. The only exit is to the south.

rooms.name: Out Over a Deep Trench
rooms.description: This rather large tree has fallen in such a nice way as to allow passage from one side of the trench to the other.  It looks sturdy enough to hold your weight, but I would not jump up and down testing it as you are perched high above the ground should you fall.
